---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import workyScreenshot1 from "@assets/images/worky-screenshot-1.png";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
---

<BaseLayout>
  <div class="space-y-8 font-['Crimson_Pro'] text-stone-700">
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <h1 class="text-5xl font-semibold leading-[1.2] tracking-tight">
        Worky
      </h1>
      <p class="text-[1.2rem]">
        A macOS app that helps you organize and access your files efficiently.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
        <img alt="Swift" src="https://img.shields.io/badge/Swift-FA7343?style=for-the-badge&logo=swift&logoColor=white" />
        <img alt="SwiftUI" src="https://img.shields.io/badge/SwiftUI-0066CC?style=for-the-badge&logo=swift&logoColor=white" />
        <img alt="macOS" src="https://img.shields.io/badge/macOS-000000?style=for-the-badge&logo=apple&logoColor=white" />
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 pt-2">
        <a
          href="https://github.com/cin4ed/worky"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg border border-stone-200 bg-white px-4 py-2 text-[1.1rem] text-stone-700 transition-all hover:border-stone-300 hover:bg-stone-50"
        >
          <svg class="h-5 w-5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor">
            <path d="M12 0c-6.626 0-12 5.373-12 12 0 5.302 3.438 9.8 8.207 11.387.599.111.793-.261.793-.577v-2.234c-3.338.726-4.033-1.416-4.033-1.416-.546-1.387-1.333-1.756-1.333-1.756-1.089-.745.083-.729.083-.729 1.205.084 1.839 1.237 1.839 1.237 1.07 1.834 2.807 1.304 3.492.997.107-.775.418-1.305.762-1.604-2.665-.305-5.467-1.334-5.467-5.931 0-1.311.469-2.381 1.236-3.221-.124-.303-.535-1.524.117-3.176 0 0 1.008-.322 3.301 1.23.957-.266 1.983-.399 3.003-.404 1.02.005 2.047.138 3.006.404 2.291-1.552 3.297-1.23 3.297-1.23.653 1.653.242 2.874.118 3.176.77.84 1.235 1.911 1.235 3.221 0 4.609-2.807 5.624-5.479 5.921.43.372.823 1.102.823 2.222v3.293c0 .319.192.694.801.576 4.765-1.589 8.199-6.086 8.199-11.386 0-6.627-5.373-12-12-12z"/>
          </svg>
          View on GitHub
        </a>
        <a
          href="https://www.producthunt.com/p/worky/worky"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg border border-stone-200 bg-white px-4 py-2 text-[1.1rem] text-stone-700 transition-all hover:border-stone-300 hover:bg-stone-50"
        >
          <svg class="h-5 w-5" viewBox="0 0 512 512" fill="currentColor">
            <path d="M496 256c0 137-111 248-248 248-25.6 0-50.2-3.9-73.4-11.1 10.1-16.5 25.2-43.5 30.8-65 3-11.6 15.4-59 15.4-59 8.1 15.4 31.7 28.5 56.8 28.5 74.8 0 128.7-68.8 128.7-154.3 0-81.9-66.9-143.2-152.9-143.2-107 0-163.9 71.8-163.9 150.1 0 36.4 19.4 81.7 50.3 96.1 4.7 2.2 7.2 1.2 8.3-3.3.8-3.4 5-20.3 6.9-28.1.6-2.5.3-4.7-1.7-7.1-10.1-12.5-18.3-35.3-18.3-56.6 0-54.7 41.4-107.6 112-107.6 60.9 0 103.6 41.5 103.6 100.9 0 67.1-33.9 113.6-78 113.6-24.3 0-42.6-20.1-36.7-44.8 7-29.5 20.5-61.3 20.5-82.6 0-19-10.2-34.9-31.4-34.9-24.9 0-44.9 25.7-44.9 60.2 0 22 7.4 36.8 7.4 36.8s-24.5 103.8-29 123.2c-5 21.4-3 51.6-.9 71.2C65.4 450.9 0 361.1 0 256 0 119 111 8 248 8s248 111 248 248z"/>
          </svg>
          View on Product Hunt
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="aspect-video w-full rounded-lg bg-stone-100">
      <Image src={workyScreenshot1} alt="Worky Screenshot" class="w-full h-full object-cover rounded-lg" />
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold">About</h2>
        <p class="text-[1.2rem]">
          Worky is designed to streamline your workflow by letting you create custom file groups
          that can be instantly accessed from your desktop. Whether you're juggling multiple
          projects or need quick access to frequently used files, Worky makes file organization
          effortless.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold">Key Features</h2>
        <ul class="list-inside list-disc space-y-2 text-[1.2rem]">
          <li>Create and manage multiple workspaces for different projects</li>
          <li>Import entire directories as workspaces with a single click</li>
          <li>Easy switching between workspaces to declutter your desktop</li>
          <li>Move files seamlessly between different workspaces</li>
          <li>Quick workspace cleanup to restore your desktop's original state</li>
          <li>Intuitive file management with drag-and-drop support</li>
          <li>Native macOS experience with minimal resource usage</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold">Documentation</h2>
        <p class="text-[1.2rem]">
          A comprehensive manual is available with detailed instructions on installation, 
          getting started, and making the most of Worky's features. 
          <a 
            href="https://deep-filament-1f1.notion.site/Worky-Manual-e56cd184f40e43839b47a4e0b46c28bd"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 hover:underline"
          >
            View the full documentation â†’
          </a>
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold">Technology</h2>
        <p class="text-[1.2rem]">
          Built using Swift and SwiftUI for a native macOS experience, Worky takes advantage
          of the latest Apple technologies to provide a smooth and efficient file management
          solution. The app includes Sparkle integration for seamless automatic updates,
          ensuring users always have access to the latest features and improvements.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold">Journey & Recognition</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-[1.2rem]">
          <p>
            Worky represents my first complete journey in app development - from conception to public launch. 
            I managed the entire lifecycle of the application, including development, testing, and distribution through web channels.
          </p>
          <p>
            The app gained significant recognition on Product Hunt, receiving over 100 upvotes and being featured in their 
            top 10 daily product newsletter. A particularly memorable moment was receiving a positive review from 
            Product Hunt's creator <a class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 hover:underline" href="https://www.producthunt.com/@rrhoover" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Ryan Hoover</a>, validating the app's utility and design.
          </p>
          <p>
            This project marked several important milestones in my development career: acquiring my first paying customers,
            generating my first income from a self-developed application, and learning valuable lessons about the importance
            of marketing in product success. These experiences provided invaluable insights into the full spectrum of
            launching a successful software product.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
